  "text": "The parameters descriptive of DQ interactions with the cuvette in the absence of cells, k 2 ϭ 0.028 min Ϫ1 and k Ϫ2 ϭ 0.051 min Ϫ1 , were previously obtained from DQ concentration vs. time experiments carried out in the absence of cells [CITATION_1] . The model parameters to be estimated were the apparent maximum rates of NQO1-mediated DQ reduction to DQH 2 , mitochondrial electron transport complex III-mediated DQH 2 oxidation to DQ, and their corresponding Michaelis-Menten constants. The steps for fitting the kinetic model to the data were analogous to those used previously to evaluate DQ redox reaction kinetics mediated by normal endothelial cells [CITATION_2] . First, to obtain the V max1 and K m1 for the NQO1-mediated reduction pathway, Eq. 9 was fit to the DQ-mediated Fe(CN) [CITATION_3] 3Ϫ reduction rate vs. DQ concentration data in Fig. 3 (dashed line) . The estimated V max1 values were 0.32 and 0.73 nmol per min Ϫ1 per cm 2 for the normoxic and hyperoxia-exposed cells, respectively, and the values for K m1 were 1.8 and 3.9 M for the normoxic and hyperoxia-exposed cells, respectively.",
